1
00:00:20,980 --> 00:00:21,579
Ruoxi,

2
00:00:22,140 --> 00:00:22,859
is that you?

3
00:00:24,900 --> 00:00:25,859
It's me.

4
00:00:26,699 --> 00:00:27,499
Jiasheng,

5
00:00:28,580 --> 00:00:30,900
why did you handle it this way?

6
00:00:31,980 --> 00:00:33,019
Why?

7
00:00:33,499 --> 00:00:34,460
What way?

8
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:37,219
Why did you handle it this way?

9
00:00:37,819 --> 00:00:39,139
Answer me!

10
00:00:42,180 --> 00:00:43,419
Because this way

11
00:00:44,260 --> 00:00:45,620
is safe for both of us.

12
00:00:50,779 --> 00:00:52,180
Safe for both?

13
00:00:52,620 --> 00:00:53,419
Jiasheng,

14
00:00:55,019 --> 00:00:56,139
don't you recognize me?

15
00:00:56,180 --> 00:00:57,300
Get away!

16
00:00:58,019 --> 00:00:59,580
I'm dead.

17
00:01:00,419 --> 00:01:02,620
You're living like a walking corpse.

18
00:01:03,019 --> 00:01:04,099
Neither human

19
00:01:04,099 --> 00:01:05,419
nor ghost.

20
00:01:06,180 --> 00:01:07,620
How is this safe?

21
00:01:07,699 --> 00:01:08,580
If

22
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:12,859
I had taken An Ruoxi

23
00:01:13,699 --> 00:01:15,419
and Su Yunian's form,

24
00:01:16,419 --> 00:01:18,299
would our story's ending have

25
00:01:19,460 --> 00:01:20,620
been different?

26
00:01:20,820 --> 00:01:21,820
Get away!

27
00:01:22,219 --> 00:01:23,180
Tu Jiasheng!

28
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:25,579
There's never been any An Ruoxi here.

29
00:01:25,820 --> 00:01:28,620
This is all your delusion.

30
00:01:29,939 --> 00:01:30,779
I...

31
00:01:31,059 --> 00:01:31,939
Jiasheng.

32
00:01:32,260 --> 00:01:34,219
I am the real one.

33
00:01:34,620 --> 00:01:35,499
I'm leaving.

34
00:01:36,939 --> 00:01:38,020
Yunian is here.

35
00:01:38,779 --> 00:01:39,980
She'll take care of you.

36
00:01:41,312 --> 00:01:42,499
Treat her well.

37
00:01:43,779 --> 00:01:44,900
Don't let her down.

38
00:01:47,219 --> 00:01:48,020
Jiasheng,

39
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:50,419
be good to Yunian.

40
00:01:51,699 --> 00:01:52,939
Be a normal person.

41
00:01:54,020 --> 00:01:55,699
Those secrets are too heavy.

42
00:01:56,540 --> 00:01:57,779
They'll crush you.

43
00:01:59,299 --> 00:02:00,219
Break free.

44
00:02:01,820 --> 00:02:02,579
Will you?

45
00:02:03,299 --> 00:02:03,939
Don't go.

46
00:02:04,779 --> 00:02:05,499
Ruoxi,

47
00:02:06,380 --> 00:02:07,180
don't go.

48
00:02:08,139 --> 00:02:09,020
Come back!

49
00:02:12,384 --> 00:02:15,616
=The Glory Fades=

50
00:02:15,616 --> 00:02:18,336
=Episode 21=
(Break Free)

51
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:44,060
(I set the AC to 26 degrees.)

52
00:02:44,448 --> 00:02:46,100
(The special hangover remedy is ready.)

53
00:02:47,072 --> 00:02:49,260
(The front desk's pressing your coat.)

54
00:02:49,579 --> 00:02:50,619
(I'm stepping out.)

55
00:02:50,739 --> 00:02:51,780
(Be back later.)

56
00:03:01,248 --> 00:03:03,040
(26°C)

57
00:03:13,660 --> 00:03:15,019
Hello, this is Chu Bai.

58
00:03:15,419 --> 00:03:16,500
Chu Bai,

59
00:03:17,019 --> 00:03:18,500
I knew you'd contact me.

60
00:03:19,139 --> 00:03:20,220
Tell me what to do.

61
00:03:27,419 --> 00:03:27,940
Jiasheng,

62
00:03:28,699 --> 00:03:29,660
she is with me.

63
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:32,000
If you want, I'll hand her over anytime.

64
00:03:32,699 --> 00:03:33,739
But Feng said

65
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:35,299
it'll take a few days.

66
00:03:35,780 --> 00:03:37,780
He doesn't want more trouble now.

67
00:03:37,980 --> 00:03:39,540
Who wants to keep her,

68
00:03:40,179 --> 00:03:41,540
you or Feng?

69
00:03:42,540 --> 00:03:43,619
I want to keep her.

70
00:03:47,419 --> 00:03:48,780
Then keep her if you want.

71
00:03:49,220 --> 00:03:50,459
Don't use Feng to pressure me.

72
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:51,980
Just three days.

73
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:53,540
Three days later,

74
00:03:53,699 --> 00:03:54,579
bring her to me.

75
00:03:55,980 --> 00:03:56,579
And

76
00:03:57,019 --> 00:03:57,619
Lu,

77
00:03:59,100 --> 00:03:59,940
I should thank you.

78
00:04:00,739 --> 00:04:01,699
What for?

79
00:04:02,299 --> 00:04:03,139
Thank you

80
00:04:04,340 --> 00:04:05,540
for not lying to me.

81
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:14,299
You heard everything.

82
00:04:14,739 --> 00:04:15,699
I can't protect

83
00:04:15,699 --> 00:04:16,500
what Jiasheng wants.

84
00:04:18,179 --> 00:04:19,060
I'll try.

85
00:04:19,820 --> 00:04:21,220
But I genuinely don't know

86
00:04:21,579 --> 00:04:22,619
where she is now.

87
00:04:25,419 --> 00:04:27,059
I thought you arranged her hiding spot.

88
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:29,580
She said she had her own safe place.

89
00:04:42,460 --> 00:04:43,419
You mean

90
00:04:43,419 --> 00:04:45,379
someone sent this video

91
00:04:45,379 --> 00:04:46,859
to your email?

92
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:48,700
What does this sender

93
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:49,859
actually want?

94
00:04:52,299 --> 00:04:53,939
I've analyzed several possibilities.

95
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:55,379
First,

96
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,100
he's a righteous bystander

97
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:59,220
who knows the secrets.

98
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,100
But fearing Tu Jiasheng's power,

99
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:02,112
he won't speak openly

100
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:04,100
and send me emails

101
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:05,100
anonymously.

102
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:06,179
Second,

103
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:07,819
he's Tu Jiasheng's enemy.

104
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:10,179
He deliberately found the footage

105
00:05:10,179 --> 00:05:11,220
and spliced it together

106
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:12,419
to confuse me.

107
00:05:12,619 --> 00:05:13,340
The purpose

108
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:15,379
is to get back at Tu Jiasheng.

109
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:16,859
Of course,

110
00:05:17,140 --> 00:05:18,259
third,

111
00:05:19,499 --> 00:05:20,100
he

112
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:21,340
is the murderer.

113
00:05:23,819 --> 00:05:24,739
All these coincidences

114
00:05:25,419 --> 00:05:27,460
might have been arranged
by him in advance.

115
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:30,460
But the person caught in this video

116
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:34,020
really does look like Tu Jiasheng.

117
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:36,540
Yet I don't think he'd kill Ruoxi.

118
00:05:40,819 --> 00:05:42,020
You mean this?

119
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:46,780
All his clothes are pressed at my place.

120
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:48,660
I'm certain he owns this bespoke suit.

121
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:56,780
Seems

122
00:05:56,980 --> 00:05:58,432
I need to learn more

123
00:05:58,432 --> 00:05:59,540
about their past.

124
00:06:00,580 --> 00:06:01,299
At least,

125
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:03,020
I need to understand Tu Jiasheng

126
00:06:03,460 --> 00:06:04,379
better.

127
00:06:25,299 --> 00:06:26,739
I thought you were full yesterday.

128
00:06:26,980 --> 00:06:28,660
- Why are you wolfing it down today?
- Madam.

129
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:29,939
What's going on?

130
00:06:30,580 --> 00:06:31,299
Slow down.

131
00:06:31,499 --> 00:06:34,048
These are stray cats.
Mr. Tu takes care of them.

132
00:06:34,048 --> 00:06:35,059
Easy. There's plenty.

133
00:06:40,179 --> 00:06:40,980
You know what?

134
00:06:42,379 --> 00:06:43,220
You lot

135
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:44,419
are from the same litter.

136
00:06:45,419 --> 00:06:46,848
You're the biggest food guarder.

137
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:47,900
Don't run away!

138
00:06:48,340 --> 00:06:49,376
Run off when I scold you.

139
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,819
Sharing food

140
00:06:51,020 --> 00:06:52,580
is what brothers should do.

141
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:53,619
Go play.

142
00:06:56,739 --> 00:06:58,580
Can't blame it for being assertive.

143
00:06:58,700 --> 00:06:59,619
To survive,

144
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:01,499
you have to fight when you need to.

145
00:07:01,980 --> 00:07:02,939
This is

146
00:07:02,939 --> 00:07:04,299
human instinct.

147
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:05,819
No,

148
00:07:06,419 --> 00:07:07,819
cat instinct.

149
00:07:12,419 --> 00:07:13,340
He didn't stop you?

150
00:07:13,739 --> 00:07:15,140
I'm Madam now.

151
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,179
Why would he stop me?

152
00:07:18,220 --> 00:07:18,700
Right,

153
00:07:19,379 --> 00:07:19,900
Madam.

154
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:21,220
Where are you going, Madam?

155
00:07:21,379 --> 00:07:23,419
Seeing you are so kind,

156
00:07:23,419 --> 00:07:24,819
taking care of strays,

157
00:07:25,179 --> 00:07:26,220
I'll treat you.

158
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:29,460
Here.

159
00:07:56,939 --> 00:07:57,980
So you know.

160
00:07:58,419 --> 00:07:59,179
Know what?

161
00:08:00,499 --> 00:08:02,419
Live and eat like a normal person.

162
00:08:03,419 --> 00:08:05,056
I thought you only knew how to lord it

163
00:08:05,056 --> 00:08:06,020
over people.

164
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,179
Depends on who it is.

165
00:08:10,340 --> 00:08:11,140
What about with Ruoxi?

166
00:08:15,140 --> 00:08:16,059
She often

167
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:17,379
brought me here.

168
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:18,379
(We're here.)

169
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:19,619
(This is the spot.)

170
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:21,780
Should we try somewhere else?

171
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:23,900
If you want noodles,

172
00:08:23,939 --> 00:08:25,020
a chain place is there.

173
00:08:25,020 --> 00:08:26,020
Not bad, I've tried it.

174
00:08:27,619 --> 00:08:28,819
We're eating here.

175
00:08:33,419 --> 00:08:34,220
This place...

176
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:38,220
Mr. Tu Jiasheng,

177
00:08:38,739 --> 00:08:39,700
I hope

178
00:08:39,940 --> 00:08:41,980
you can live a worldly life.

179
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:43,899
Stop being so high and mighty.

180
00:08:44,779 --> 00:08:45,940
Trying to become immortal?

181
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:50,139
Madam An Ruoxi,

182
00:08:51,139 --> 00:08:52,820
isn't Deep In The Bustle

183
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:54,940
worldly enough?

184
00:08:58,220 --> 00:08:58,940
No,

185
00:08:59,460 --> 00:09:00,460
not even close.

186
00:09:01,180 --> 00:09:02,420
Its glitz and glamour

187
00:09:02,539 --> 00:09:04,420
is a place for a few to unwind.

188
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:07,100
For most, it's just gossip over tea.

189
00:09:15,499 --> 00:09:16,700
Don't you think

190
00:09:17,779 --> 00:09:19,499
it's happy for two people

191
00:09:19,820 --> 00:09:20,940
to work together,

192
00:09:21,619 --> 00:09:22,779
leave work together,

193
00:09:23,420 --> 00:09:24,739
cook a meal,

194
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,739
pick up kids from school,

195
00:09:27,180 --> 00:09:28,499
watch them grow up slowly,

196
00:09:29,019 --> 00:09:30,739
and care for aging parents?

197
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:40,659
Their lives might not be rich,

198
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:43,019
but loving each other as family,

199
00:09:43,539 --> 00:09:44,700
that's happiness.

200
00:09:49,820 --> 00:09:50,420
Ruoxi,

201
00:09:52,379 --> 00:09:53,539
have a child with me.

202
00:09:54,139 --> 00:09:55,259
Boy or girl, either's fine.

203
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:01,340
What?

204
00:10:01,619 --> 00:10:02,539
Not willing?

205
00:10:02,980 --> 00:10:03,820
I hope

206
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:05,619
if we have a child,

207
00:10:06,499 --> 00:10:07,980
we can give them a stable life.

208
00:10:08,139 --> 00:10:09,180
Isn't it stable now?

209
00:10:09,619 --> 00:10:10,499
Is it?

210
00:10:10,779 --> 00:10:11,420
Ruoxi,

211
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:12,700
I said it before

212
00:10:13,619 --> 00:10:14,980
your ideas are unrealistic.

213
00:10:15,619 --> 00:10:17,420
But you're walking a knife's edge.

214
00:10:20,379 --> 00:10:21,300
So

215
00:10:21,379 --> 00:10:23,180
she wanted you to close
Deep In The Bustle.

216
00:10:26,779 --> 00:10:27,779
So what is it?

217
00:10:28,779 --> 00:10:30,016
Is Deep In The Bustle

218
00:10:30,016 --> 00:10:31,220
so unrealistic?

219
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:33,152
Why can't I feel it?

220
00:10:33,899 --> 00:10:35,460
How is it walking a knife's edge?

221
00:10:37,259 --> 00:10:38,739
This is your difference.

222
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:56,064
Any other questions?

223
00:10:56,064 --> 00:10:56,619
Go ahead.

224
00:10:58,619 --> 00:10:59,899
I'm afraid if I ask,

225
00:11:00,340 --> 00:11:01,220
you'll get angry.

226
00:11:01,820 --> 00:11:02,779
I won't get angry.

227
00:11:06,619 --> 00:11:07,619
On November 5th,

228
00:11:08,019 --> 00:11:09,340
the day Ruoxi's killed,

229
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:11,300
to be precise,

230
00:11:11,499 --> 00:11:12,420
during that period,

231
00:11:13,779 --> 00:11:14,820
where exactly were you?

232
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:16,499
You still don't trust me.

233
00:11:17,779 --> 00:11:19,259
Whether I trust you is one thing.

234
00:11:19,739 --> 00:11:20,899
Answering me directly

235
00:11:20,899 --> 00:11:21,859
is another.

236
00:11:23,379 --> 00:11:24,180
That day,

237
00:11:25,180 --> 00:11:26,180
I met Mr. He,

238
00:11:26,779 --> 00:11:28,619
He Cong's father,
the one who bullied you.

239
00:11:29,536 --> 00:11:30,259
No.

240
00:11:30,619 --> 00:11:32,060
Your dinner with him

241
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:33,700
started at 7:30 PM.

242
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:35,580
Only Mr. Zhao went that day.

243
00:11:36,499 --> 00:11:37,504
Mr. He and his secretary

244
00:11:37,504 --> 00:11:38,700
were growing impatient.

245
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:40,659
At 9:12 PM,

246
00:11:40,940 --> 00:11:42,820
you finally returned to Room 333.

247
00:11:44,180 --> 00:11:45,259
Am I wrong,

248
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:46,539
Mr. Tu?

249
00:11:48,420 --> 00:11:49,420
How do you know?

250
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:53,659
Don't want to answer?

251
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:55,580
Or difficult to answer?

252
00:12:01,499 --> 00:12:02,259
What?

253
00:12:02,539 --> 00:12:03,499
After a meal,

254
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,220
you're not Madam anymore?

255
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:07,379
Let's talk elsewhere.

256
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:16,700
Mr. Tu really is powerful.

257
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:18,019
Even the monitors are live.

258
00:12:19,779 --> 00:12:20,980
Point out without telling.

259
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:31,180
Ms. Bai!

260
00:12:34,739 --> 00:12:35,460
- Ms. Bai!
- Ms. Bai!

261
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,460
Not answering my calls, huh?

262
00:12:42,859 --> 00:12:44,619
Playing dead and disappearing?

263
00:12:49,139 --> 00:12:50,460
(To: Bai Ruxue)
(Call me back now.)

264
00:12:50,580 --> 00:12:51,379
(Or else...)

265
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,739
(From: Bai Ruxue)
(Ms. Bai, I'll give you an address.)

266
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:56,180
(Let's meet and talk.)

267
00:13:08,460 --> 00:13:09,700
Ms. Bai,

268
00:13:10,259 --> 00:13:11,460
welcome!

269
00:13:33,220 --> 00:13:34,980
So this is your hiding place?

270
00:13:36,220 --> 00:13:37,779
How does it feel?

271
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:39,539
Can this be considered paradise?

272
00:13:40,940 --> 00:13:42,139
Oh, Ruxue!

273
00:13:42,940 --> 00:13:44,019
Gained some skills!

274
00:13:45,859 --> 00:13:47,180
After following you for years,

275
00:13:47,180 --> 00:13:48,659
I should have learned something.

276
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:53,100
Feng arranged for you?

277
00:13:56,259 --> 00:13:57,779
You really live up to your name,

278
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,340
truly clever.

279
00:14:00,499 --> 00:14:01,820
Here, try this.

280
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:03,779
These are roses from my backyard.

281
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:05,659
I dried and brewed this tea myself.

282
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:06,980
It has a rich aroma.

283
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:08,300
You'll love it.

284
00:14:18,899 --> 00:14:19,739
Where's Feng?

285
00:14:19,940 --> 00:14:20,779
I want to see him.

286
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:23,379
How is it?

287
00:14:23,379 --> 00:14:24,340
Do you like the taste?

288
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:25,220
I'm asking you.

289
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:27,180
Where is Feng?

290
00:14:29,499 --> 00:14:30,300
Ms. Bai.

291
00:14:31,379 --> 00:14:32,539
Why have you become

292
00:14:32,539 --> 00:14:34,379
not so smart anymore?

293
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:36,259
Feng

294
00:14:36,379 --> 00:14:38,539
is someone you can just ask to see?

295
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:40,619
Bai Ruxue,

296
00:14:43,019 --> 00:14:44,499
I told you long ago.

297
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:46,060
Stay away from troubles.

298
00:14:46,060 --> 00:14:47,139
Stay away from troubles.

299
00:14:47,139 --> 00:14:48,340
Focus on my duty.

300
00:14:48,340 --> 00:14:48,940
Right?

301
00:14:49,859 --> 00:14:51,619
But my dear sister!

302
00:14:51,619 --> 00:14:52,980
What is trouble?

303
00:14:52,980 --> 00:14:54,180
What is duty?

304
00:14:54,779 --> 00:14:55,980
Can you even tell them apart?

305
00:15:00,980 --> 00:15:03,379
Your Highness, your tea.

306
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:07,940
Mr. Nie,

307
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:11,700
I thought
your son lives abroad for years.

308
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:13,300
Your Highness,

309
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:15,619
he only returned home last month.

310
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:17,060
Do you think

311
00:15:18,180 --> 00:15:19,659
if he is capable

312
00:15:19,779 --> 00:15:21,259
of shouldering the responsibility?

313
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:33,980
Raise your head.

314
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:35,580
Let me get a look at you.

315
00:15:45,899 --> 00:15:47,220
Your son

316
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,539
has remarkably sharp eyes,

317
00:15:50,060 --> 00:15:51,700
as if countless needles

318
00:15:51,940 --> 00:15:54,779
of different sizes and thickness
hid in it.

319
00:15:58,700 --> 00:15:59,499
Very well.

320
00:15:59,659 --> 00:16:00,980
Let me taste this tea.

321
00:16:04,499 --> 00:16:05,460
Rise.

322
00:16:11,499 --> 00:16:13,100
No matter what Feng tells you,

323
00:16:14,659 --> 00:16:15,619
you need to understand

324
00:16:17,019 --> 00:16:18,180
Mr. Tu will never let you go.

325
00:16:18,180 --> 00:16:19,259
Of course, I know.

326
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:23,259
He loves slaughter game the most.

327
00:16:23,659 --> 00:16:24,499
People

328
00:16:24,580 --> 00:16:25,539
tend to show off

329
00:16:25,899 --> 00:16:27,379
what they lack most.

330
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:29,499
What's your real purpose
for meeting me today?

331
00:16:31,779 --> 00:16:32,820
Just be patient.

332
00:16:32,980 --> 00:16:33,659
Have some tea.

333
00:16:34,379 --> 00:16:35,379
Come on.

334
00:16:36,180 --> 00:16:37,379
Bai Ruxue,

335
00:16:38,899 --> 00:16:40,619
if this is your attitude,

336
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:42,499
I can only have people

337
00:16:42,499 --> 00:16:43,739
hand you over to Mr. Tu.

338
00:16:45,499 --> 00:16:47,180
I truly regret asking Lu to help you.

339
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:50,180
Fine.

340
00:16:50,779 --> 00:16:52,060
Then arrest me and take me back.

341
00:16:54,060 --> 00:16:55,899
Do you think I don't dare?

342
00:16:59,580 --> 00:17:00,180
Go ahead.

343
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:01,379
What are you waiting for?

344
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:06,420
Then come with me.

345
00:17:07,739 --> 00:17:08,379
Fine.

346
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:09,700
Let's go.

347
00:17:15,019 --> 00:17:16,700
Bringing me back

348
00:17:16,980 --> 00:17:17,980
isn't a big win,

349
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:19,819
but it's making up for your mess.

350
00:17:30,388 --> 00:17:34,062
♪If the heart can't hear the sorrow♪

351
00:17:34,361 --> 00:17:37,552
♪It only makes everything look so fake♪

352
00:17:39,264 --> 00:17:43,005
♪Your eyes resemble hers too much♪

353
00:17:43,554 --> 00:17:46,353
♪Who makes me forget whom♪

354
00:17:47,824 --> 00:17:51,554
♪The warmth in my heart is fading♪

355
00:17:51,778 --> 00:17:55,275
♪Every glance feels like atonement♪

356
00:17:56,674 --> 00:18:00,361
♪Ambiguity hidden in the night breeze♪

357
00:18:00,999 --> 00:18:06,114
♪Blows away the chance to explain♪

358
00:18:06,818 --> 00:18:10,952
♪I feel guilty♪

359
00:18:11,522 --> 00:18:15,266
♪I'll have no regrets
even I leave quietly♪

360
00:18:16,130 --> 00:18:19,573
♪Even in tears♪

361
00:18:20,322 --> 00:18:24,236
♪It doesn't matter♪

362
00:18:24,418 --> 00:18:28,241
♪We embrace in dreams♪

363
00:18:28,992 --> 00:18:32,704
♪I let down all my defenses♪

364
00:18:33,762 --> 00:18:37,440
♪Though the story has its end♪

365
00:18:37,890 --> 00:18:46,242
♪I'll journey with you all my life♪
